From: grante@hydro.rosemount.com (Grant Edwards)
Subject: Re: Yggdrasil Hassles  -- response from YCI
Date: Wed, 3 Nov 1993 19:17:28 GMT

Yggdrasil Computing (yci@netcom.com) wrote:

:       I sent some email to the original poster offering to send him a
: copy COD if he'd send his physical mail address.  Yggdrasil ships all
: US orders by UPS Red, so the original poster would have received his
: order by 10:30am tomorrow if he had responded.

I think he's talking about me, and they did offer to ship it COD at no
extra charge.  But, I can't afford to burn a day of vacation time to
sit at home and wait for the UPS man.  

I was going to call some of their resellers, but t turned out to be a
moot point -- I found out that somebody at the office had already
purchased the disk.  

As I related in previous posts, I did a "complete" install, and am
pretty happy with my system.  Getting the pl13 sources from sunsite
solved all of the problems that I ran into when trying to recompile
the kernel.

If you've got 250M of space for the complete install, I can recommend
LGX.  Others seem to have had more hassles doing a runtime install and
selectively installing packages.

