Crossposted-To: comp.os.linux.help
From: dwb@ITD.Sterling.COM (David Boyd)
Subject: Anyone have text/ps autodetection printcap/filter setup
Date: Wed, 3 Nov 1993 20:00:35 GMT

Oh hail all you wise and generous Linux gurus out there:

        Has anyone setup the neccessary printcap entry and filters to support
automatic recognition of the file type by lpr for printing to a postscript
printer.  I have a ps printer hooked to my TAMU based linux system and
would like to be able to transparently print text and postscript files
without needing to remember to run the filters.  I can set up a shell
script as a filter to do this but I hate re-inventing the wheel.  I am
primarily interested in text and postscript detection but other formats
(Troff, GIT, etc) would also be usefull.  Thanks for the help in advance.

